  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed combinations. Thirteen credibility factors were assessed. The package decision is recorded as Accepted on the basis that hemolysis predictions remained below the clinical threshold in all nominal operating points; however, two factors carry achieved levels that fall short of the required levels for MRL 5, a structural shortfall that the rationale does not explicitly resolve.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-below-clinical-limit",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-mrl5",
